Embedded vs web development skill list.

Here's a comparison of the core skills for **Embedded Development** and **Web Development**.

| Skill              | Embedded Development                    | Web Development                                   |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| Primary Languages  | C, C++, Rust                            | Java, C#, Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Go, PHP |
| Operating Systems  | Bare Metal, RTOS, Embedded Linux        | Linux, Windows, Cloud Linux                       |
| Memory Management  | Very important                          | Moderate (depends on language)                    |
| Hardware Knowledge | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Essential                         | ⭐ Minimal                                         |
| Networking         | TCP/IP, CAN, UART, SPI, I2C             | HTTP, HTTPS, WebSocket, REST, gRPC                |
| Multithreading     | RTOS tasks, interrupts                  | Threads, async programming                        |
| Debugging          | JTAG, GDB, Logic Analyzer, Oscilloscope | IDE debugger, logs, profilers                     |
| Databases          | Rare                                    | PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis                 |
| Cloud              | Optional                                | AWS, Azure, GCP                                   |
| Containers         | Rare                                    | Docker, Kubernetes                                |
| APIs               | Device drivers, HAL                     | REST, GraphQL, gRPC                               |
| Security           | Secure Boot, Firmware Signing           | OAuth, JWT, TLS, Authentication                   |
| CI/CD              | Firmware pipelines                      | GitHub Actions, Jenkins, GitLab CI                |
| Testing            | Hardware-in-the-loop, Unit Tests        | Unit, Integration, E2E, Load Testing              |
| Version Control    | Git                                     | Git                                               |
| Build Systems      | CMake, Make, Bazel                      | Maven, Gradle, npm, pip                           |

### Embedded Development Roadmap

* C/C++
* Data Structures & Algorithms
* Computer Organization
* Microcontrollers (STM32, AVR, ESP32)
* Digital Electronics
* UART, SPI, I2C, CAN
* RTOS (FreeRTOS, Zephyr)
* Embedded Linux
* Device Drivers
* Networking (TCP/IP)
* Debugging with GDB/JTAG
* CMake, Make
* Git

### Web Development (Backend) Roadmap

* Java / C# / Python / Go / Node.js
* Data Structures & Algorithms
* OOP & Design Patterns
* SQL (PostgreSQL/MySQL)
* REST APIs
* Authentication (JWT, OAuth)
* Redis
* Message Queues (Kafka, RabbitMQ)
* Docker
* Kubernetes
* AWS/Azure/GCP
* CI/CD
* Monitoring (Prometheus, Grafana)
* System Design
* Git

### Which is harder?

* **Embedded:** Harder at the low level because you need to understand hardware, memory, timing, interrupts, and electronics.
* **Web:** Broader ecosystem with many frameworks and tools, but generally less hardware complexity.

If you **don't want to work in embedded systems** and are interested in **Java backend/cloud development**,
focusing on the web backend skill set (Java + Spring Boot + PostgreSQL + Docker + AWS + System Design) aligns better with your career goals.
